fields.value: Harris 1989 Perceptions of Cleveland Survey, study no. 892038

dsDescriptionValue.value: This survey focuses on specific perceptions about Cleveland among key local and national audiences. It as designed to gather the information needed to steer a community marketing program, and to provide a benchmark to measure the program's effectiveness.

fields.value: Subject: Study Level Error Note, Notes: Interviews were conducted in two groupings: (1) within a four-county Cleveland area and (2) nationally, excluding the four-county Cleveland area.;Type: ODUM:ACCESS.CATEGORY Notes: I;Type: ODUM:CODEBOOK.NUMBER Notes: H-892038;
